>Jeremy, you turned out to be on the ball.
>I had to buy an entire arm/switch assembly.
>The steering wheel lifted right off, though, & the
>horn button  I could remove easily.
>In fact, it was MUCH easier than replacing the starter
>motor, which I've done before.
>For the record, the steering wheel nut on the '77 was
>a 24mm nut.
>In fact, I had to buy a socket especially to do the
>job.
