>--- jeremy norris <psychfellow(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:
> > Well, you probably already got it fixed, but i will
> > reply anyway. I have a
> > 77 and the same EXACT thing happened to me a few
> > weeks ago. you have to buy
> > a new turn indicator lever assembly. i spent about
> > 28 usdollars on one.
> > then, you use a knife to pop off the horn button.
> > then, you use a 17mm
> > socket (i think it was 17, maybe bigger) to undo the
> > nut in the center of
> > the wheel. Then, you use your knees to pull the
> > wheel off. Then you look up
> > under the plastic by your knees and see where all
> > the wires go. you pull the
> > wires down, the old assembly comes off with just a
> > little patience. you
> > slide the wiper switch off first. put the new lever
> > on, put the wiperswitch
> > on, and reassemble everything. took me about 20
> > minutes, i would double
> > check the torque setting on the steering wheel nut,
> > just to be safe. good
> > luck!
> > -jeremy
